### LineBuffer class
Handles chunk-to-line buffering for streaming output:
```typescript
class LineBuffer {
  private buffer = '';
  constructor(private onLine: (line: string) => void) {}
  push(chunk: string) {
    this.buffer += chunk;
    const lines = this.buffer.split('\n');
    this.buffer = lines.pop()!;
    lines.forEach(l => this.onLine(l));
  }
  flush() { if (this.buffer) { this.onLine(this.buffer); this.buffer = ''; } }
}
```

### Timeout Strategy
Use AbortSignal + Promise.race for exec timeout. Default 30s.
Stream has no default timeout — caller provides AbortSignal.

